Government Orders: -

According to the provisions of Section 4 (4) and 4 (5) of the Maharashtra Prevention of Delay in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005, the following officers, who are awaiting appointment to the cadre of Deputy Collectors, are required to appear in front of their name on administrative grounds / request in Column No. The post indicated in section 4 is being posted with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and administrative convenience.

As the above mentioned officers are awaiting appointment, they are required to join the new post immediately. The date on which the officer concerned appeared in place of the new appointment should be immediately communicated to the Government by e-mail / post at e2.revenue@maharashtra.gov.in.

3. The officers concerned shall be liable to disciplinary action under the provisions of the Representation of the People Act, 1950 and the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct of Business) Rules, 1979, if they are found not to have joined the place of transfer before the expiry of the period of office, in accordance with the said provisions prescribed under Rule 15 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption, non-acceptance of service and Provisions during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981.

The officers concerned during the prescribed period as per the rules of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption of office, non-attachment of service and service during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981.
